Abiodun Nejo, Ado Ekiti The Independent Corrupt Practices and other Related Offences Commission has decried the “shoddy execution of some constituency projects” of National Assembly members in Ekiti State. ICPC Chief Superintendent in charge of tracking programmes in Ekiti State, Azeez Lawal, said the sanctions for the contractors for such projects would be prosecution or for them to return to the site. Lawal spoke in Ado Ekiti on Friday after tracking of constituency projects undertaken in Ikere and Ekiti southwest council areas of the state. READ ALSO: 2023: I knew Buhari was deceiving Tinubu – Afenifere chieftain, Adebanjo He said, “From what we saw so far, some of the jobs were well done, some were not properly done and such is not encouraging.” According to him, the aim of the ongoing second phase of tracking of the National Assembly members’ constituency projects for 2016, 2017 and 2018 “is to know if the jobs are being done, if they are/were properly done, if they are not done at all, or if there are infractions”. “If there are infractions, the contractors will face the wrath of the law. We will write our reports. The decision on appropriate sanctions will be taken by the ICPC management. It is either they tell the contractors to go back to the site or they will be taken to the courts for prosecution,” Lawal said.